obo:UBERON_0002421  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_4718  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2a, S6: Pulldowns with GST-FCHO2 in rat brain lysate identified known Clathrin Coated Pit (CCP) proteins eps15, eps15R and intersectin 1&2 as main interaction partners.\n\nFigure S4: overexpression of FCHO2 in DIV4 rat hippocampal neurons showed co-localization with clathrin at distinct neurite puncta (S4b, low resolution). Clathrin signals within neuronal cell bodies (endosomes, pericentriolar area) remained in FCHo1+2 RNAi (knockdown) neurons, but not the puncta on neurites (S4c). Furthermore, SYT1 surface expression was increased (S4d) and SYP fluorescence was decreased following induced exocytosis (S4e) upon FCHo1+2 knockdown, indicating a decrease of CME and SV recycling.\n\nAuthors showed FCHO2 is involved in Clathrin-Mediated Endocytosis and is localized at Clathrin Coated Pits (CCP) in HeLa cells using high-resolution EM and live cell imaging. Next, authors showed FCHO2 interacts with known synaptic CME proteins, co-localizes with CCPs at neurites in rat brain lysate and knockdown affects SV endocytosis. Although imaging resolution is too low to pin-point localization to pre/post-synapse (or both), these results imply FCHO2 is localized at synapses and involved in CME.. Experimental description: Figure 2a: \"Pull down with GST-FCHo2-μHD and rat brain lysate\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-07-31" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4718" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

